# Credentials for `npm run release` (scripts/publish.ts).
#
#   cp publish.env.example publish.env    <- publish.env is gitignored;
#                                            it must NEVER be committed.
#
# NPM_TOKEN - an npm Granular Access Token:
#   1. npmjs.com -> avatar -> Access Tokens -> Generate New Token -> Granular
#   2. Packages and scopes: Read and write, scoped to @cube-drone, with
#      "bypass 2FA" so publishes run unattended
#   3. Expiry: your call - shorter is safer, renewal is this same dance
#
#   THIS FILE IS THE BOOTSTRAP, NOT THE SYSTEM: both registries require a
#   package to exist before trusted publishing can be configured for it, so
#   the first release uses these tokens - and after configuring trusted
#   publishing for every package/crate (see RELEASING.md), REVOKE them.
#   Subsequent releases are `npm run release -- --tag-only` + the release
#   workflow, with no stored tokens anywhere. (Also the reason not to
#   mourn the token: npm sunsets 2FA-bypass direct publish ~January 2027.)
NPM_TOKEN=

# CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN - a crates.io API token:
#   1. crates.io -> avatar -> Account Settings -> API Tokens -> New Token
#   2. Scopes: publish-new + publish-update
#      (crate scope: cube-drone-marquee-* once the crates exist)
CARGO_REGISTRY_TOKEN=

# Future registries land here as the ecosystems grow (see RELEASING.md):
# VSCE_PAT=   - VS Code Marketplace (Azure DevOps Personal Access Token)
# OVSX_TOKEN= - Open VSX (Eclipse account token)
